---
# Worked-example project BRIEF demonstrating per-doc `rubric_overrides`
# and `target_length_overrides` shapes (issue #296 — BRIEF.md absorbs all
# project-level anvil config; the prior `<thread>/.anvil.json` carrier is
# retired).
#
# This example shows TWO non-investment-memo shapes from the studio canary
# (2026-06-02), each calibrated for its own subtype:
#
#   1. `synthesis-brief` — a decision-framework portfolio synthesis
#      (~11K words) reading across a bundle of vertical briefs, market
#      models, and framing companions. The reader (CEO) is expected to
#      extract the framework and apply judgment; the memo is deliberately
#      non-prescriptive on the portfolio-shape choice. (Modeled on the
#      brasidas-synthesis canary thread.)
#
#   2. `feedback-memo` — a studio-side feedback memo TO a CEO on his draft
#      roadmap thesis (~5K words). Validates parts, recommends sharpening,
#      proposes a concrete pitch backbone. No "the company," no ask, no
#      founder section — the recommendation target is positional. (Modeled
#      on the raytheon-pitch-strategy canary thread.)
#
# To use: copy this file to `<project>/BRIEF.md`, drop the leading comments,
# trim or extend the documents list to match your project, and tune the
# calibration prose / target ranges to your threads. See
# `anvil/skills/memo/SKILL.md` §"Rubric overrides and non-investment-memo
# shapes" for the full contract.

project: studio-2026-q2
audience:
  - Studio CEO (primary)
  - Strategic partners (secondary)
hard_rules:
  - Cite every load-bearing claim with a defensible mechanism.
  - Recommendations must be falsifiable; name the evidence that would flip them.

documents:
  - slug: brasidas-synthesis
    artifact_type: descriptive-thesis
    target_length: { words: [9000, 13000] }
    # Per-version overrides on top of `target_length`. Each key is the
    # version number (as a string); the value is `[min, max]` shaped
    # the same way as `target_length`. The resolver applies
    # `target_length_overrides["<N>"]` first, then `target_length`, then
    # the implicit "reasonable for the decision" fallback.
    target_length_overrides:
      "1": { words: [10000, 14000] }   # v1 carries scaffolding; bigger budget
      "2": { words: [9000, 13000] }    # v2 compresses; steady-state range
    rubric_overrides:
      memo_subtype: synthesis-brief
      dim_1_calibration: >-
        decision-framework — score on framework clarity + sub-recommendation
        sharpness, not on single ranked recommendation. This brief is
        intentionally non-prescriptive on the strategic shape choice; it
        commits clearly to several sub-recommendations but explicitly defers
        the portfolio-shape choice to the reader. Do not score down dim 1
        for "no single recommendation" — score dim 1 on whether the decision
        framework itself is clearly stated and whether the sub-recommendations
        are sharp.
      dim_5_calibration: >-
        defers to underlying market models — score on integration quality
        not on fresh sizing. This brief deliberately defers detailed market
        sizing to the underlying per-vertical market models in the analytical
        bundle. Score this dimension on whether the synthesis correctly
        integrates the model outputs into the strategic framework, not on
        whether the synthesis itself does original market sizing.
      dim_6_calibration: >-
        defers to underlying market models — score on whether financial
        framing supports positioning, not on whether the synthesis itself
        does original financial modeling. The per-vertical scenario math
        lives in the bundle; the synthesis's job is to integrate the
        outputs, not to re-derive them.
      dim_7_calibration: >-
        target length 9000-13000 words; score against declared target, not
        against a 2000-3000 word investment-memo expectation. This brief is
        materially longer than a typical investment memo because it
        synthesizes ~75K words of source material; the declared range
        reflects the synthesis-brief shape, not scope creep.
      target_length: { words: [9000, 13000] }

  - slug: raytheon-pitch-strategy
    artifact_type: position-paper
    target_length: { words: [4000, 6000] }
    # Per-document iteration-cap paired override (issue #349). BOTH keys
    # are required when overriding — setting `max_iterations` without a
    # non-empty `iteration_cap_rationale` is a schema violation at parse
    # time. The override may raise the cap but not lower it below the
    # principled default (4); `< 4` is rejected.
    #
    # Sticky-raise semantics: setting `max_iterations: 5` raises the cap
    # to 5 until the BRIEF is edited again. The required rationale —
    # preserved in BRIEF git history — is the audit trail that documents
    # why this thread deserves more revision passes than the principled
    # default. See `anvil/skills/memo/SKILL.md` §"Per-document override
    # contract" for the full validation contract.
    max_iterations: 5
    iteration_cap_rationale: |
      Operator-extended to 5 on 2026-06-08. v4 verdict 34/44 vs floor
      35; gap is positional-framing-side (Recommendation §3 conditional
      terms could be sharpened, reviewer named dim 4 at 5/6 with
      specific suggestion). One extra reviser pass to close the gap;
      founder follow-ups for source-side lift tracked separately.
    rubric_overrides:
      memo_subtype: feedback-memo
      dim_1_calibration: >-
        feedback-to-third-party — score on position clarity (does the memo
        take a clear position on the engaged document and propose a concrete
        next move?), not on single ranked investment recommendation. This
        memo has no "the company" and no check-size ask; the recommendation
        target is positional, not financial. Do not score down dim 1 for
        "no invest/pass/conditional recommendation" — score dim 1 on whether
        the positional recommendation (validate / sharpen / replace / extend)
        is unambiguous and whether the proposed pitch backbone (or equivalent
        next-move artifact) is concrete.
      dim_4_calibration: >-
        feedback-memo — score dim 4 on whether the memo names the risks of
        the position it is recommending the third party adopt, not on whether
        it names the operating risks of a portfolio company. The relevant
        risk surface is positional (where could the proposed sharpening /
        pitch backbone fail to land?), not operational.
      dim_5_calibration: >-
        secondary for feedback-memo shape — score dim 5 on whether market
        framing supports the positional recommendation, not on whether the
        memo does original TAM/SAM/SOM sizing. Feedback memos engage a
        third party's existing positioning; the load-bearing question is
        whether the proposed sharpening matches the market the third party
        is actually in, not whether the memo independently sizes that market.
      dim_6_calibration: >-
        secondary for feedback-memo shape — score dim 6 on whether the
        financial framing supports the positional recommendation, not on
        whether the memo does original unit-economics or scenario modeling.
        Feedback memos do not carry an investment ask; financial reasoning
        enters only insofar as it pressure-tests the positional recommendation.
      dim_7_calibration: >-
        target length 4000-6000 words; score against declared target.
        Forceful brevity is load-bearing for this shape — every other
        rubric dim rewards additions, so the dim 7 anchor must hold the
        line on the declared range. A feedback memo that drifts long has
        typically over-defended a position the operator wanted stated
        forcefully and moved on from.
      target_length: { words: [4000, 6000] }
---

# Project: studio-2026-q2 — worked-example BRIEF

This BRIEF demonstrates the issue #296 consolidated config shape: every
project-level and per-doc anvil knob lives in this file's YAML frontmatter,
and the prior sibling `<thread>/.anvil.json` is retired. The two
`documents:` entries above show:

- **Per-doc `target_length`** — the document-level default range (words
  or pages; the resolver converts pages to words at 600 wpp per the
  SKILL.md convention).
- **Per-doc `target_length_overrides`** — per-version overrides applied
  on top of the default. Keys are version-number strings (`"1"`, `"2"`,
  …); values are `{ words: [min, max] }` or `{ pages: [min, max] }`.
- **Per-doc `rubric_overrides`** — the subtype-calibration block from PR
  #265 (issue #233). Carries `memo_subtype`, per-dimension calibration
  prose (`dim_N_calibration`), and an optional `target_length` override
  scoped to the subtype.
- **Per-doc `max_iterations` + `iteration_cap_rationale`** — the
  paired iteration-cap override from issue #349 (demonstrated on the
  `raytheon-pitch-strategy` entry above). BOTH keys are required when
  overriding; the rationale text is the audit trail preserved in BRIEF
  git history. The override may raise the cap above the principled
  default of 4 but never lower it. See `anvil/skills/memo/SKILL.md`
  §"Per-document override contract" for the full validation contract.

Free prose below the frontmatter is shared project context — author voice,
audience notes, hard-rule rationale. The reviewer reads this prose as
"BRIEF context" during `memo-review`; the per-doc structured metadata
above drives the mechanical wiring (overlay selection, target-length
resolution, calibration-suffix attachment).

For projects with only one document and no calibration needs, the
frontmatter can be much shorter:

```yaml
---
project: my-simple-project
audience: [me]
hard_rules: []
documents:
  - slug: thesis-memo
    artifact_type: investment-memo
    target_length: { words: [2000, 3000] }
---
```

That minimal shape is byte-equivalent (in behavior) to a project with no
calibration overrides — the reviewer applies the base /44 rubric and the
investment-memo overlay (identity), the drafter / reviser honor the
declared `target_length`, and no per-dimension suffix attaches in
`scoring.md`. The non-trivial shape above only kicks in when at least one
per-doc `rubric_overrides:` block is present.
